<br>
Your first order of business, once you can manage the team, is to bench Tidus. He can do Jecht's Shot, which is cool, but his abilities are not up to par with what you want your team to be.<br>
<br>
Next, sign Wedge, who is standing right outside the hallway which is the entrance to the Auroch's locker room in Luca. He will be your one of your shooters, so his position will be LF. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
Then, wait until you meet a person named &quot;Brother&quot;, and sign him. He is your other shooter, your RF. There's a goalie I rather liked that I found near the shrine to Yojimbo, and another one after the shoopuf ride. Nadia who works the shop in the Calm Lands is a good defender.<br>
<br>
Other than that, try to find somebody to be your center forward (with good pass) and another defender (with good attack).<br>
<br>
Once you get Brother going, the fun really begins. First of all, he is by far the fastest player in the game. He starts with 75 speed, and gets faster with levels. I have him up to 84 speed, and ALL of his stats are high. Your strategy should be based around him and Wedge. From a blitzoff, if you win, you should move your CF (who will have the ball) straight towards the goal, until their CF comes to guard him. Immediately turn around and go towards your goal, and see how they're playing you. If there's just one defender on Brother, odds are he can score. If there are two close by, he can probably outrun at least one going for the goal. Pass him the ball, and rush straight towards the goal. Always break the defender when shooting if  you think you have a chance, and use a technique shot, if necessary, to boost your shot.<br>
<br>
So what if you don't win the blitzoff? Here's where it pays to have Brother and Wedge, both of whom have good attack. The computer does one of three things from blitzoff, and approximate likelihoods for each action:<br>
-Rushes the middle forward (50%)<br>
-Rushes the right forward (25%)<br>
-Rushes the left forward (25%)<br>
<br>
If they rush the middle forward, you'll often get 3 people into the break, which means you'll probably end up with the ball. If you can Nap Tackle, here is a great place to do it, because a sleeping middle forward for the computer means a wide open court... or whatever. From here, you'll have to see what the computer is giving you. <br>
-<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong> If they are all bunched up on their half of the court,</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> here is where you get the ball to Brother immediately. Try to go to the bottom half of the court, and get the defenders there to chase you. Once you get into their range, they'll follow you endlessly, or until you're out of their range. Stupid!! Brother is too fast, so they probably (heck, never) will catch him, and once you have a little bit of separation from the pack, toss the ball to Wedge, who should be wide open. Goooooooooooooooooal!<br>
-<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong> If they are spread out over the court,</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> a good middle forward is very helpful. Move him up the court, and sometimes everyone will converge on him. Before they get in range of forcing a break, pass the ball to one of your shooters.<br>
-<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong> If you see an imbalance towards the left or the right (top or bottom, on the map),</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> pass the ball back to one of your defenders on the open side, and move them as far down the edge of the court as you can. Try to pull a defender off a shooter by moving close then running away, and you'll find a wide open goal.<br>
<br>
That's about all there is to it. I really like having a team where everyone can attack, block, and pass well, and two good shooters. Speed kills, and Brother is a mass murderer. <br>
<br>
As your Blitzball team progresses, I suggest you watch and see who the computer does not re-sign to a new contract. ESPECIALLY Al-Bhed players. If an Al-Bhed is not re-signed, GO GET THEM!! They are so insanely better than everyone else.<br>
<br>
If you want to gain experience, remember it's not that important. The computer's level is the average level of your team, except they get more skills. If you get an extremely powerful front 3, you'll hardly even use your defenders, so it might be a good idea to let them throw the ball amongst each other if your opponenet allows it. In fact, I often go for stretches of game where the computer doesn't so much as get a shot to the goalie, so your front 3 can totally dominate the court.<br>
<br>
If you want to get the Sigil for Wakka's legendary weapon, here's what you do:<br>
1) Win a league<br>
2) Choose &quot;Back&quot; instead of &quot;Continue Playing Blitzball...&quot; when the option comes up<br>
3) Save.<br>
4) Play blitzball.<br>
5) Look and see what the first prize is for league. If it's not the Sigil, hold L1, L2, R1, R2, start, and select to reset the game.<br>
